<br>
Been trolling the boards for a long time with a few posts along the way.  Just dinged 101 AA pts and want to give you my thoughts and what skills I have bought.<br>
<br>
Run3<br>
Regen 3<br>
Int5 - went for AC and Hp prior ro the rod nerf and was at 220 int - also spent 4 points in pop int.  With some recent upgrades my int is 245.<br>
<br>
SCM3 - the best skill out there.<br>
SCF3 <br>
Mental Clarity 3 - lots of controversy but having innate mana regen3 is great.<br>
<br>
Pet Hold -definite must have.<br>
Mend Companion - followed by haste mend 3 - 9 min recast time on a 1980 pt heal.  This rocks for solo.<br>
Water Elem 1 - looks cool but wish it had a faster recast time.<br>
Next class skill will be QS 2 and Elemental pact - for faster pet canni.<br>
<br>
Pop Int 4<br>
<br>
Suspeneded Minion 2 - this skill is fantastic.  Get a pet up and buffed/armed/ds, suspend, invis yourself and run to your camp with a pet ready to go.  Also, great for pet canni - I use MS2 combined with summoning efficency3, conj spec and and SCM3, fm comes fast, and will be faster with QS2.<br>
Host of Element 3 - impresses the yokels, does a nice piece of damage and if you are quick you can surround the mob with 9 pets = )<br>
Fury5 - Just bought, and from what I have read it's a 12% crit chance - I have noticed more crits =p<br>
<br>
So, there are lots of ways to go.  SCM3 is a must.  I like the idea of trying to save as much mana as possible, followed by maximizing mana regen and finishing it with a large mana pool.<br>
<br>
Ciao,<br>
<br>
Jonmc Cascadian<br>
ArchConvoker Dark Breed of Norrath<br>
