There is no one &quot;true&quot; way that's better than any other. - Eloina<br>
======<br>
<br>
Absolutely. There are only optimal ways for various playstyles, and of course, those who follow those playstyles unsurprisingly choose the best approachs and hunting grounds for themselves. Which is why people have different opinions.<br>
<br>
To someone who doesn't use PC, and I know many who practically never do, and especially to those who bias toward groups and almost never raid, QS is not an exciting or vital skill, and EP and IR are as useful as Innate Charisma.<br>
<br>
To someone like Jochan, they are vital and worth their weight in gold.<br>
<br>
To recommend to other magi, listen to all and decide for yourselves, based on your own playstyle. Horses for courses, all things in balance.<br>
<br>
======<br>
You cannot ever tell me that your Evocation path, highly dependent on outside buffs, is superior to the Efficiency path, which requires none. EVER. - Jochan<br>
======<br>
<br>
More arrogance, defining YOUR path as 'the' Efficiency path. It isn't. And yes, I just did tell you the evocationalist path is superior to the PC one, at least, for many magi it is, even if it is not for you.<br>
<br>
I'll remember when a chanter comes ask me for focus items for KEI when I log in tonight, as happens many nights, to say no, as that would be powerlevelling myself (and him!) ROFL. Geez I've heard some nonsense in my time ... LOL<br>
<br>
Keep making sweeping and condescendingly arrogant statements on public messages boards, giving biased, unbalanced and even plain bad advice to others, and you will keep getting refuted.<br>
<br>
It seems, noone can have a different opinion than Jochan without being 'WRONG'.<br>
<br>
I'm done here. I don't go attacking your posts on other threads, even if I think you are talking manifest nonsense. Kindly give me the same respect, and we do not have to have these 'exchanges'.<br>
<br>
/bow<br>
<br>
Suzanna.<br>
